-- #799 review follow-up: the ELetGroup/`where` eager-reference guard added for
-- #799 must be SOURCE-ORDER-AWARE. `evalLetGroup` (eval.mdk) evaluates a
-- nullary where-binding EAGERLY IN SOURCE ORDER, so a BACKWARD reference to an
-- EARLIER sibling (`b` referencing `a`, `a` already installed) reads an
-- already-set cell and is perfectly safe — only a self- or FORWARD reference
-- (to a cell not yet installed) is the Ref-VUnit hazard. An earlier version of
-- the guard flagged ANY sibling reference regardless of order and wrongly
-- REJECTED this ordinary, working `where` shape. check == run == build all
-- ACCEPT and agree on the value (106).
f x = b
  where
    a = x + 1
    b = a + 100

main = println (f 5)
